# Google Analytics Integration Guidelines

## Client Initialization
Initialize the GA client once and reuse:
```typescript
const analyticsClient = new BetaAnalyticsDataClient();
```

## Date Range Handling
Use the standardized date range utility:
```typescript
function getDateRange(timeframe?: string): DateRange {
  // Support standard timeframes:
  // - today
  // - yesterday
  // - this week
  // - last week
  // - this month
  // - last month
  // Default to last 30 days if not specified
}
```

## Metric Definitions
Define clear interfaces for each metric type:
```typescript
interface EngagementMetrics {
  averageSessionDuration: number;
  bounceRate: number;
  engagedSessions: number;
  screenPageViewsPerSession: number;
}

interface TrafficSource {
  source: string;
  medium: string;
  pageViews: number;
  users: number;
}
```

## Query Construction
- Use type-safe dimension and metric definitions
- Include appropriate filters and date ranges
- Handle pagination for large result sets
- Implement retry logic for failed requests

## Data Aggregation
- Group metrics by appropriate time periods (daily/monthly)
- Provide both raw and aggregated data
- Include metadata with response
- Cache frequently requested data

## Error Handling
- Handle GA4 API specific errors
- Provide fallback values where appropriate
- Log detailed error information
- Implement circuit breakers for rate limits

## Performance
- Batch requests when possible
- Use appropriate sampling rates
- Cache responses with reasonable TTL
- Monitor API quota usage
